-- Turkish Prosecutors Question Pianist on Religion, Vatan Reports
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2012-05-16T08:46:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/turkish-prosecutors-question-pianist-on-religion-vatan-reports.html
Turkish prosecutors summoned pianist
Fazil Say for questioning following comments about religion
posted on Twitter, Vatan  reported .  Say, who served as a European Union culture ambassador in
2008, testified yesterday after prosecutors received a complaint
alleging that the pianist had incited public enmity and insulted
religious values with comments posted on Twitter, according to
the Istanbul-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  